The Trusters platform will activate tomorrow, Tuesday, February 3rd, at 12:00 PM (UTC+1), a strategic opportunity in the heart of Tuscany. The Residencia Puccini Project seeks capital for the renovation and functional adaptation of a Florentine-style building complex at Via del Ponte alle Mosse 180, Florence. With a guaranteed minimum annual return of 10.50%, this operation is positioned as one of the most attractive in the Italian market due to its risk-reward profile.

Investment Summary  

Project Name: Residencia Puccini.  

Estimated Return: 10.50% minimum annual (scalable based on investment ticket and Early Bird bonus).  

Term: 18 months (estimated closing in 15 months after fundraising).  

Location: District 1 - Historic Center (San Jacopino), Florence.  

Objective: Creation of 12 Class A Energy-Efficient homes.

The Asset: Florentine Tradition and Modern Efficiency  

The project consists of the comprehensive renovation of a building comprising the first, second, and third floors. The intervention not only seeks to rehabilitate the structure but to transform the space to meet contemporary standards of sustainability and comfort.

Work Details  

Distribution: Creation of 12 new residential units with commercial areas between 50 and 60 square meters.  

Energy Efficiency: Installation of latest-generation aerothermal systems (heat pumps) and thermal insulation on roofs and facades to achieve Class A certification.  

Current Status: The property has already been acquired by the Proponent, administrative documentation (SCIA) is approved, and demolition and roof insulation works began in November 2025.  

Total Area: Approximately 660 sqm of residential space, excluding common areas and annexes.

Return Structure and "Early Bird" Benefits  

Trusters introduces an incentive system based on investment volume and booking speed. Investors participating during the Pre-Booking phase will receive an additional +1.00% on their annual ROI (except for the first tier).

The Developer: Guarantee of Solvency and Track Record  

The operation is led by the group composed of RS Investment Srl and Area Immobiliare, under the direction of Rosario Saporito. This developer is one of Trusters' most reliable historical partners, with a Quality A rating.

Success History on the Platform:  

The group has fully repaid all previous projects on Trusters, often ahead of schedule.  

Total volume returned: Over â‚¬4,500,000 (principal + interest).  

Recent Examples: Projects on Via di Villa Demidoff and Via Massaia were repaid in periods ranging from 7 to 13 months, beating the initial 15-month estimates.

Location and Market: San Jacopino  

The property is located in a high-demand area in District 1 - Historic Center. San Jacopino is a strategic neighborhood due to its proximity to the Novoli university campus, the San Donato shopping center, and the Cascine Park, Florence's largest green lung. Additionally, it has a direct connection via the T02 tram line between the central station and the airport, ensuring excellent commercial exit for the homes.

